<subSubSection pageId="307" pageNumber="308" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="307" pageNumber="308">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindroth" authorityYear="1961" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Broscodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="307" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Broscodera</taxonomicName>
Lindroth, 1961b: 150. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1852" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Miscodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="307" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="307" pageNumber="308">Miscodera insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mannerheim, 1852 by original designation. Etymology. From the generic name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1813" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Broscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="307" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="307" pageNumber="308">Broscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="307" pageNumber="308">q.v</emphasis>
.] and the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="307" pageNumber="308">dere</emphasis>
(neck, by extension pronotum) [feminine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="307" pageNumber="308" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="307" pageNumber="308">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="307" pageNumber="308">
Northern Hemisphere, with four species in the Nearctic (one species) and Palaearctic (three species) Regions arrayed in two subgenera: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindroth" authorityYear="1961" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Broscodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="307" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="307" pageNumber="308">Broscodera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.str. (one species) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deuve" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sinobrosculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="307" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="307" pageNumber="308">Sinobrosculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Deuve (three species in Nepal, Gansu, and Sichuan).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
